 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow  - (x - a)\left| {\matrix{
   {x + a} &amp; {x - c}  \cr 
   {x + b} &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right| + (x - b)\left| {\matrix{
   {x + a} &amp; 0  \cr 
   {x + b} &amp; {x + c}  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow  - (x - a)\{  - (x + b)(x - c)\}  + (x - b)(x + a)(x + c) = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow (x - a)(x + b)(x - c) + (x - b)(x + a)(x + c) = 0$$<br><br>If we put x = 0 in LHS<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow (0 - a)(0 + b)(0 - c) + (0 - b)(0 + a)(0 + c)$$<br><br>$$ = abc - abc = 0$$<br><br>which satisfies the above equation<br><br>Hence, x = 0.

